article.headline: VA Commonwealth 84, Hampton 44
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- B.A. Walker had 16 points and Virginia Commonwealth held Hampton to 25 percent shooting as the Rams won their sixth straight, 84-44, Friday night. The Rams (8-2) had four players in double digits, and their reserves outscored the Pirates' 45-19. Nick George added 12 points, and Alexander Harper and Jamal Shuler had 10 apiece. Bruce Brown led Hampton (1-7) with 11 points and nine rebounds. The Rams stole the ball 10 times, had nine blocked shots and scored 22 off Hampton turnovers. VCU also outscored Hampton 16-0 off the fast break and sank 10-of-25 3-pointers. VCU has won eight of its last nine.
